Self-Attention Mechanism Instead of processing text sequentially like older models (e.g., RNNs, LSTMs), Transformers process all words at once while giving different "attention" to different parts of the text. This allows context-aware responses without the limitations of sequential memory. Multi-Head Attention Each input token is analyzed from multiple perspectives (heads), allowing richer understanding of meaning. Positional Encoding Since Transformers do not process words in order, a positional encoding system tells the model where each word belongs in a sequence. Layer Normalization & Feedforward Networks Transformer layers have fully connected neural networks that adjust activations dynamically, improving efficiency.
